<Font|headerFont>OPTIONS<Font|helpFont><p><p>

The options menu is accessible at any time by pressing the ESC key. From
the
options menu, you have access to the following option categories.<p><p>

<Font|subheaderFont>GRAPHICS DEVICE<Font|helpFont><p><p>

These options can be adjusted to make the game work optimally with your
graphics device. Your current Allegiance graphics
settings appear at the bottom of the menu. Note that these settings, with
the exception of Brightness, are only in effect while flying in
space.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>To access the options for your graphics device<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpbullet|Press ESC, D.><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Brightness Up/Down -- <Font|helpFont>Click these
options, or press the
U or D key, to adjust to higher or lower brightness, respectively. If no
change occurs, you are already at the highest or lowest brightness or your
graphics device does not allow adjustment of this setting.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Higher/Lower Resolution -- <Font|helpFont>Click these
options, or press the H or L key, to adjust to higher or lower resolution,
respectively. If no
change occurs, you are already at the highest or lowest resolution.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>3D Acceleration -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option, or press the A key, to toggle your 3D acceleration on and
off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Secondary Device -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option, or
press the S key, to toggle your secondary graphics device on and
off.<p><p>

At the bottom of this menu, you will see your current graphics
device settings.<p><p>

<Font|subheaderFont>GRAPHICS OPTIONS<Font|helpFont><p><p>

If you find your frame rate needs a boost, try turning off any one or
combination of the game graphics options.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>To access the options for game graphics<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpbullet|Press ESC, O.><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Environment -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or
press the E key, to toggle the background environment
on and off. Environmental graphics look great but are not necessary.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Posters -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the P key, to toggle poster
items on and off. These are large background bitmap graphics such as nebulae and planets.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Debris -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the D key, to toggle general space debris on and off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Stars -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the S key, to toggle the background stars on and off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Strobes -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the R key, to toggle
station and ship lights on and off. If you turn them off, you can still
see
the proper landing hangar by the color green inside the hangar bay.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Trails -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the T key, to toggle the
trails of ships on and off. Note, however, that these trails are a great
way
to tell who is on your team quickly, as the trail color matches the team
color.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Afterburner Smoke -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option, or press the A key, to toggle the exhaust of ships on and
off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Lens Flares -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or
press the F key, to toggle lens flares on and off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Bidirectional Lighting -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option, or press the B key, to toggle bidirectional
lighting on and off. Bidirectional lighting is a dramatic second light source that adds a
greater feeling of depth to objects, but it is not mandatory.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Style -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option, or press
the H key, to toggle your HUD style between Normal and
Software modes. Software is a good option if you want to try and improve your frame rate.<p><p>

<Font|subheaderFont>SOUND OPTIONS<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>To access the options for sound<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpbullet|Press ESC, S.><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Sound Quality -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option to
cycle
through the sound quality settings. Higher quality sound also means a
heavier hit on your processor so you might want to reduce your sound
quality to keep a good frame rate.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Sound Card Acceleration -- <Font|helpFont>Click
this option to toggle your sound card's acceleration on and off. If you
have any sound problems, try turning off the acceleration.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Music -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option to toggle
background music on and off.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Music Volume -- <Font|helpFont>Click these
options, or press the corresponding key, to increase (M) or decrease
(N) music volume.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Sound Effect Volume -- <Font|helpFont>Click these
options, or press the corresponding key, to increase (S) or decrease
(A) the sound effects.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Voiceover Volume -- <Font|helpFont>Click these
options, or press the corresponding key, to increase (V) or decrease (C)
the voiceover in the training missions and the message stream chat.<p><p>

<Font|subheaderFont>GAME OPTIONS<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>To access input options<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpbullet|Press ESC, G.><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Censor Display -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the S key, to toggle between censoring and not censoring your
messages. If you censor your messages, you will be protected from foul
language.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Default View -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the K key, to set your default view to either Cockpit
view or Chase view.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Filter Chats Sent to All -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option,
or press the A key, to toggle between filtering and not filtering
messages that are sent to all players in the game.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Filter Voice Commands -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option,
or press the Q key, to toggle between filtering and not filtering all
voice commands.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Filter Chats Sent from Lobby -- <Font|helpFont>Click
this option,
or press the F key, to toggle between filtering and not filtering all
messages that come from players in the Team Lobby.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Control Response -- <Font|helpFont>Click this
option, or press the L key, to toggle between Quadratic
and Linear control response. If your joystick is too sensitive, try
the quadratic response.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Dead Zone -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the Z key, to toggle between a normal and a large
area around which your joystick is considered centered in the middle of your screen.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Virtual Joystick -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the J key, to toggle between using your mouse as a virtual and a
nonvirtual joystick. <p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Y Axis -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the Y key, to toggle between a normal and a flipped Y axis
on your joystick. When the Y axis is flipped, pushing the joystick
forward will point the nose of your craft upward instead of
downward.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Force Feedback -- <Font|helpFont>Click this option,
or press the E key, to toggle between turning on and off the
feedback on a joystick that has this feature.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Map Keys and Controls -- <Font|helpFont>Click or
press C to
<Main|hlpc7c|adjust your input settings> in the Configure Controls dialog
box.